section.t:
This memo discusses a solution where:
					the server learns a fundamental characteristic of the path during the 1-RTT phase;
					the server sends that information to the client at the end of the 1-RTT phase;
					the server and the client exploit that information to improve the time-to-service during subsequent 0-RTT connections.

A new extension named "BDP_data" is defined for NewSessionTicket. It contains the following value: BDP_value, that is the value in bits (same unit as ). The reception of the field BDP_data provides the client with 3 indications:
						The path with this server has a large BDP;
						The server added the path characteristics in the opaque 'ticket' field;
						The server will optimize the reopening of the session upon reception of this opaque ticket.
